    "nickname": "LuckyDuke",
    "content": "Interesting challenge, for all kind of programmers.\nThe description is clear, original, and tells a story.\n\nIt's a good idea to deactivate 'Reverse mode', I don't think recovering the logic and the different factors would be an interesting task!\nThe different tests are meaningful.\n\nI find the size of code mode particularly interesting.\nMay I suggest you two different solutions?\n\nAn optimized version of yours:\nprint(sum('X A B AB X O'.split().index(t[:-1])*(2+('-'in t))for t in(input()for _ in[0]*int(input()))))\n\nAnother way of doing it:\nprint(sum((('A'in t)+(2*('B'in t))+(5*('O'in t)))*(2+('-'in t))for t in open(0)))\n\nThank you for your contribution!",
    "codingamerHandle": "c8fc65229597c0f35b0c060147d6f18e2832275",
